                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13476206" author="tabish121" created="Mon, 15 Oct 2012 15:32:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested this against the 5.7 release and this is not happening, the code doesn&apos;t encode headers until after the CONNECTED frame is sent and the protocol version is set.  Reopen if you can provide a JUnit test case that reproduces this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13476520" author="gmallard" created="Mon, 15 Oct 2012 22:18:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apologies, but my report of this was inaccurate and incomplete.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It only happens with: stomp+nio&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13477030" author="tabish121" created="Tue, 16 Oct 2012 14:26:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3823&quot; title=&quot;AMQ 5.6 Stomp v1.1 support fail to respect the spec and trims all ws from message headers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-3823&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-3823&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is setting the Stomp version to eagerly in the NIO case which is the problem.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13477066" author="tabish121" created="Tue, 16 Oct 2012 15:00:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
